      "summary": "The party traveled to the lean-to NW of Tagmira, previously used as a base during early Bramblewood exploration, and found a troll had taken up residence. They killed it in a brutal fight that nearly cost Sardet his life, and recovered a valuable crown and jewels. Returning to Tagmira, they learned the Bronze Host has declared the hunting grounds NW of the town off-limits, and a local hunter is missing. Pima, a young girl who uses a mirror to communicate with fairie, implored the party to defeat the Bronze Host. Tagmira is gripped by fear.",
